{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Conrad Colman | image = Conrad Colman (3).jpg | alt = A photo of Colman, dressed causally, laughing. He stands beside a furled foresail. | caption = Conrad Colman in November 2016, about to start the Vendée Globe | birth_name = | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people. For people who have died, use {{Birth date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}}. --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = New Zealand | other_names = | occupation = Yachtsman | years_active = | known_for = Single-handed yacht racing | notable_works = }} '''Conrad Colman''' is a [[yachtsman]] from [[New Zealand]]. In 2016 he became the first New Zealander to compete in the famous single-handed around-the-world race, the [[Vendée Globe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/12/02/sport/vendee-globe-sailing-foresight-natural-energy-conrad-colman/index.html|title=Vendee Globe: Conrad Colman's epic voyage|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=finish>{{cite web|url=http://www.sailingscuttlebutt.com/2017/02/24/conrad-colman-finishes/|title=Conrad Colman finishes Vendée Globe >> Scuttlebutt Sailing News|date=24 February 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=stuff>{{cite web|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/other-sports/76563521/kiwi-sailor-conrad-colman-signs-up-for-2016-edition-of-vende-globe|title=Kiwi sailor Conrad Colman signs up for 2016 edition of Vendée Globe|publisher=}}</ref> On 10 February 2017 Colman was in 10th place, 740 miles from the finish line (having completed 97% of the race's 27,440 nautical mile [[circumnavigation]]) when his [[IMOCA 60]], the ''Foresight Natural Energy'', was dismasted.<ref name="vendeeglobe-18985">{{Cite web | title = New Zealand’s Conrad Colman finishes under jury rig for 16th | publisher = Vendée Globe 2016–2017 | website = vendeeglobe.org | date = 24 February 2017 | accessdate = 25 February 2017 | url = http://www.vendeeglobe.org/en/news/18985/new-zealand-s-conrad-colman-finishes-under-jury-rig-for-16th }}</ref> Two weeks later he became the 3rd sailor in history to complete the Vendée Globe under [[jury rig]], taking 16th place in the race with a time of just under 110 days 2 hours.<ref name=finish /> Colman ran out of food after the dismasting, and completed the race on survival rations pillaged from his [[life raft]].<ref name="vendeeglobe-18985"/>
''Foresight Natural Energy'' is the same yacht that Jean-Baptiste Dejeanty used in the 2008–09 Vendée Globe<ref name=stuff /> and it is powered entirely from reusable energy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://foresightmetering.co.uk/renewable-energy-generation-onboard-foresight-natural-energy-conrad-colmans-vendee-globe-yacht/|title=Renewable energy generation onboard Foresight Natural Energy, Conrad Colman’s Vendee Globe yacht – Foresight Metering|date=22 November 2016|publisher=}}</ref> When he crossed the finish line Colman became the first skipper to comple the Vendée Globe using no fossil fuels.<ref name="vendeeglobe-18985"/>
