{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}} {{Use Australian English|date=September 2014}} {{update|date=June 2014}}
[[Queensland]] is the second largest state in [[Australia]]. It contains 472 separate [[protected areas]] with a total land area of {{convert|69388|km2|abbr=on}} (4.02% of the state’s area). 223 of these are [[National park]]s, which is the highest number of any Australian state or territory, totalling {{convert|65871|km2|abbr=on}} (3.81% of the state’s area). Seven others are Scientific National Parks, totalling {{convert|522|km2|abbr=on}} (0.03% of the state’s area).
